node.text:
For those who have spent any time in the world of cocktails and mixology, @julianthomascox is a familiar name of great renown as he is a 4 time James Beard Award Nominee and was named one of the decade's Most Influential Mixologists by Food & Wine! We teamed up with Julian to present his version of an El Silencio Margarita that is easy enough to make at home while still being sophisticated enough to impress your friend with the most knowledge of classic cocktails. 

Follow the full video and recipe below to make your own Julian Thomas Cox approved El Silencio Margarita at home! 

Ingredients 
2oz Mezcal El Silencio Espadin 
1oz Lemon & Lime Juice Blend 
1 Lime Husk 
1oz Citrus Infused Agave Syrup (1:1 Agave to Water) 
Garnish: Citrus Flake Salt Rim 

Method 
Pour flake salt into a mortar & pestle. Add lemon & lime zest and work together inside the mortar & pestle until combined. When the salt has taken on the lemon & lime zest, pour onto a flat plate. 
Rub a wedge of lime or lemon around the rim of the glass, then dip into the citrus salt. Fill the glass with ice and set aside. 
Fill a cocktail shaker with ice. 
Add Mezcal El Silencio, Lime Husk, Syrup, and Lemon & Lime Juice Blend into the ice filled shaker. 
Shake for 10 seconds. 
Strain into the prepared glass. 
Enjoy!

node.title: Julian Thomas Cox Presents: The El Silencio Margarita
